packageJSON.name: into-cps-app
packageJSON.description: User interface for the INTO-CPS Toolchain

releases.body:
## 2.2.0 (13/02/2017)

### What's New?

This is the first release of the year. This is the version of the app that is
expected to be used at the Year 2 project review.

This release contains various fixes and improvements. It also include two new
features:

* Basic Design-Space Exploration: this enables the user to execute DSE
  experiments that have been created and configured externally. 
* COE Stability Warnings: based on information in the model description files,
  the COE will monitor co-simulation stability and issue warnings in the logs
  if this is violated. This feature requires version 0.1.12 of the COE.

### Requirements

In order to open projects from Git, including the public examples import, you will need to have Git installed and available in your path.

If you want to run co-simulations, you will need the COE. It can be downloaded from the download manager inside the app. In order to run the COE, you need to have Java 8 installed. Java 8 is also required to co-simulate FMUs exported from Overture.

The app has no other dependencies and no installation is required. Simply unzip and run.

### Known Issues

There are a few known issues with the app, currently. For the full list, see https://github.com/into-cps/intocps-ui/issues.

* The COE does not terminate properly in certain circumstances. This corrupts
  the memory space of the process and any subsequent co-simulations. A
  workaround is to kill the COE process manually (via command line or task
  manager).  
* When creating/importing projects, no check is made for the root path.  The
  project will not open/import correctly if given an invalid path,.


### Problems and Troubleshooting

If you run into any problems or you simply have an idea for improvement, you can report an issue at <https://github.com/into-cps/intocps-ui/issues> or from within the app itself via `Help > Report Issue`

You can also email the WP4 mailing list for help but issue reports are vastly preferred.

### Other Resources
* [INTO-CPS Application User Manual](https://github.com/into-cps/into-cps.github.io/raw/master/manuals/INTO-CPS_User_Manual.pdf)
* [INTO-CPS Project site](http://into-cps.au.dk/)
* [INTO-CPS Release site](http://into-cps.github.io/)
* [App Developers Wiki](https://github.com/into-cps/intocps-ui/wiki)

## 2.1.8 (12/12/2016)

### What's New?

This is the last release of the year. It contains primarily bugfixes. See https://github.com/into-cps/intocps-ui/milestone/11?closed=1 for the full list.

It also includes a handful of small usability improvements:
- any missing project folders are created upon project import
- the is a button to clear the COE log
- test case coverage is displayed after running a test
- the app files should be a little smaller now

This release is also the first one to be accompanied by the INTO-CPS Application User Manual. Grab it [here](https://github.com/into-cps/into-cps.github.io/raw/master/manuals/INTO-CPS_User_Manual.pdf).

### Requirements

In order to open projects from Git, including the public examples import, you will need to have Git installed and available in your path.

If you want to run co-simulations, you will need the COE. It can be downloaded from the download manager inside the app. In order to run the COE, you need to have Java 8 installed. Java 8 is also required to co-simulate FMUs exported from Overture.

The app has no other dependencies and no installation is required. Simply unzip and run.

### Known Issues

There are a few known issues with the app, currently. For the full list, see https://github.com/into-cps/intocps-ui/issues.
- The COE does not terminate properly in certain circumstances. This corrupts the memory space of the process and any subsequent co-simulations. A workaround is to kill the COE process manually (via command line or task manager).
-  If you open several projects in  quick sessions, the app will produce an `Emit` error.
- When creating/importing projects, no check is made for the root path. The project will not open/import correctly if given an invalid path,.

### Problems and Troubleshooting

If you run into any problems or you simply have an idea for improvement, you can report an issue at https://github.com/into-cps/intocps-ui/issues or from within the app itself via `Help > Report Issue`

You can also email the WP4 mailing list for help but issue reports are vastly preferred.

### Other Resources
- [INTO-CPS Project site](http://into-cps.au.dk/)
- [INTO-CPS Release site](http://into-cps.github.io/)
- [App Developers Wiki](https://github.com/into-cps/intocps-ui/wiki)

releases.body:
## 2.1.5 (15/11/2016)

### What's New?

This is the last release of the app before the INTO-CPS November plenary. It includes various improvements and fixes, made as part of the memory stick RC. In addition to those, it includes new features to make it easier to work with test generation, including the ability to copy/delete test procedures in the project browser and viewing test generation reports directly in the app.

### Requirements

In order to open projects from Git, including the public examples import, you will need to have Git installed and available in your path.

If you want to run co-simulations, you will need the COE. It can be downloaded from the download manager inside the app. In order to run the COE, you need to have Java 8 installed. Java 8 is also required to co-simulate FMUs exported from Overture.

The app has no other dependencies and no installation is required. Simply unzip and run.

### Known Issues

There are a few known issues with the app, currently. For the full list, see https://github.com/into-cps/intocps-ui/issues
- The COE does not terminate properly in certain circumstances, which then makes it impossible to launch new simulations. A workaround is to kill the COE process
- Co-simulations occasionally crash or throw exceptions such as `java.lang.NullPointerException`, `DirectoryNotEmptyException` on Windows 64 and 
  `java.lang.RuntimeException: java.nio.file.AccessDeniedException` for 3D FMUs

### Problems and Troubleshooting

If you run into any problems or you simply have an idea for improvement, you can report an issue at https://github.com/into-cps/intocps-ui/issues or from within the app itself via `Help > Report Issue`

You can also email the WP4 mailing list for help but issue reports are vastly preferred.

### Other Resources
- [INTO-CPS Project site](http://into-cps.au.dk/)
- [INTO-CPS Release site](http://into-cps.github.io/)
- [App Developers Wiki](https://github.com/into-cps/intocps-ui/wiki)

releases.body:
## 1.1.0 (01/09/2016)

### What's New?

This release includes various UI improvements, including redesigned views for configuration and execution
of multi-models and co-simulations.

This release **breaks backwards compatibility** with previous versions of the tool chain. With this version of the app, you will need:
- COE version 0.1.2 or higher
- FMUS exported with version 0.0.3 or higher of the Overture FMU Exporter. Note that the new exporter uses a new mechanism for representing FMU variables so you will have to update your VDM models.

The public examples have gone through significant changes. It is highly recommended that you delete any existing examples and re-import them from scratch. At the time of this release, only 2 examples have been upgraded and are available for import. The remaining ones will become available for import as they are upgraded.

### Requirements

In order to open projects from Git, including the public examples import, you will need to have Git installed and available in your path.

If you want to run co-simulations, you will need the COE. It can be downloaded from the download manager inside the app. In order to run the COE, you need to have Java 8 installed. Java 8 is also required to co-simulate FMUs exported from Overture.

The app has no other dependencies and no installation is required. Simply unzip and run.

### Problems and Troubleshooting

If you run into any problems or you simply have an idea for improvement, you can report an issue at https://github.com/into-cps/intocps-ui/issues or from within the app itself via `Help > Report Issue`

You can also email the WP4 mailing list for help but issue reports are vastly preferred.

releases.name: INTO-CPS App Release 1.0.0
releases.body:
## 1.0.0 (13/06/2016)

### What's New?

Everything! This is the first official release of the app. It has several interesting features. Some of the highlights:
- Project browser
- Multi-model generation from Modelio connection mappings. To generate the mappings, you need the latest version of the [INTO-CPS Plugin](http://forge.modelio.org/projects/intocps-modelio34/files) for Modelio
- Co-Simulation configuration and execution
- Logging and live streaming of co-simulation variables
- Integrated download manager for tools and COE
- Importing of public examples
- Integration with RT-Tester
- Mockups of Model Checking and Test Data Generation UIs

Other tool chain features such as traceability and design space exploration are still being designed. Expect them in future releases.

### Requirements

In order to open projects from Git, including the public examples import, you will need to have Git installed and available in your path.

The app has no additional dependencies and no installation is required. Simply unzip and run it. To execute Co-Simulations, you will need the COE. It can be downloaded from the download manager inside the app.

### Problems and Troubleshooting

The app is still in beta so we expect there will be some issues. You can help us by reporting them at
https://github.com/into-cps/intocps-ui/issues. You can also report issues from within the app itself via `Help > Report Issue`

You can also email the WP4 mailing list for help but issue reports are preferred.

### Other Resources
- [INTO-CPS Project site](http://into-cps.au.dk/)
- [INTO-CPS Release site](http://into-cps.github.io/)
- [App Developers Wiki](https://github.com/into-cps/intocps-ui/wiki)
